    Example 11 compares to Michael Fay’s saws package. Also demonstrates implementing a two-step estimation method for GEE using geex.

    estimates <- estimate_equations(eeFUN = FAY1_eefun, 
                                data  = warpbreaks, units = 'wool', 
                                roots = c(30, .5, .5), 
                                formula = breaks ~ tension,
                                corrections_list = list(df1  = list(fun = fay_df_correction, options = list(b = 0.75, L = c(1, 1, 1), version = 2)),
                                                        bias.3 = list(fun = fay_bias_correction, options = list(b = 0.3)),
                                                        bias.75 = list(fun = fay_bias_correction, options = list(b = 0.75))),
                                family  = gaussian(),
                                alpha = .0252,
                                psi   = 141)
    saws(guo, method = 'd1')$V # 'standard sandwich method'
